{"first_name":"Niall","last_name":"Murphy","permalink":"niall-murphy","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/niall-murphy","homepage_url":"http://www.kubuventures.com","birthplace":"UK","twitter_username":"nialltweet","blog_url":"http://www.kubuventures.com/Kubu_Ventures/Kubu_Ventures/beingconnected_blog/beingconnected_blog.html","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"The Cloud","born_year":1969,"born_month":4,"born_day":16,"tag_list":"mobile-lbs-geo-internet-wireless-broadband","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Fri Nov 06 11:11:08 UTC 2009","updated_at":"Wed Jun 22 19:06:08 UTC 2011","overview":"<p>Niall is an entrepreneur, angel investor and technologist.  </p>\n\n<p>He founded Evrythng in late 2009 with Andy Hobsbawm, a software company providing active online identities for objects.  He is CEO of Ideaworks3D Limited, which trades as Marmalade and makes software that lets developers build and distribute cross-platform applications.  Niall is principal of Kubu Ventures and is actively engaged in a number of mobile and internet technology investments.  </p>\n\n<p>Previously Niall co-founded The Cloud, Europe&#8217;s leading public WiFi network operator.  The Cloud was acquired by British Sky Broadcasting in January 2011.</p>\n\n<p>Niall has authored and presented numerous papers around the world.  He was a co-author of the International Roaming Access Protocols framework in 2005, adopted by IETF as a basis for seamless WiFi roaming.</p>\n\n<p>A computer scientist by training, Niall was educated in South Africa.  He worked on telecoms policy for the African National Congress in the early 90s before embarking on a career developing technology businesses.  He was founder of one of the first internet service providers in South Africa, launched in 1994.</p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,99],"assets/images/resized/0006/5212/65212v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[214,142],"assets/images/resized/0006/5212/65212v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[214,142],"assets/images/resized/0006